Hello Tigers!
We appreciate the love and support you have given us through this transition into distance learning. Our teachers and staff have been working hard to prepare lessons and we are ready to begin tomorrow, April 6th. By now you should have been contacted by your child‚Äôs homeroom teacher. If you have not, please feel free to leave us a direct message with updated contact information and we will call you back!

We want you to know that you are not in this journey alone! We are here for you! We know you will have questions and may even be as frustrated with a homework assignment as your child is‚Ä¶fear not! We are in it together! We encourage you to contact your child‚Äôs teacher‚Ä¶

Crutcho Public School District- Home of the Tigers
March 23 at 7:49 PM ¬∑

Good evening Crutcho Families. Crutcho will provide FREE meals to support families with children ages 18 and under in the Crutcho school district area.
We will provide breakfast and lunch meals beginning Tuesday, March 24 from 10:30 am -11:00 a.m. Meals will be delivered on the student‚Äôs regular bus routes.
All Students have to do is come to their bus stop around 10:30 am and pick up the meal from the bus driver.

Guidelines do require that children must be present to receive the meals. Children can receive both meals at one time. We encourage our families to take advantage of this program that begins tomorrow. If your student is out of district you can stop by the school at 10:00 am each day to pick up a meal. Thank you!

post_text:
Crutcho Community,

This afternoon, the Oklahoma State Board of Education mandated that all schools in Oklahoma remain closed for a period of two weeks following Spring Break. This means the earliest we will resume classes would be April 6, 2020. We will continue to update our community as more information becomes available.

Our district leadership team will be meeting during this time so we can continue to serve our students. In regard to the Coronavirus (COVID-19) pandemic, please remain calm and continue to practice preventative measures such as good hand hygiene, staying home when sick, avoiding large crowds and practicing social distance.

Remember to check the district Facebook page and school website for additional information.

Reminder:
If you need to check out your student early, please notify the school prior to 3pm. For security and end of the day procedures, we cannot manage changes in transportation after that.

For example, if you know your child has a dentist appointment at 3:45, please call us before 3:00 and let us know you'll be picking them up at 3:15.

Thank you for your assistance!

post_text:
Crutcho Community!

I come to you with sad news as today, we have lost a beloved member of Crutcho Public Schools.

Cindy Alexander started her service at Crutcho Public Schools 7 years ago, spending several years in the elementary school working with the STEM program, before joining the middle school team this past August as middle school teacher. Soon as funeral arrangements are made available we will share them.

We understand that many of you may have upsetting feelings and questions about Ms. Alexander‚Äôs death. We will try to answer any questions that we can. At times like this, it is okay to have many different feelings, including sadness, anger, and disbelief. It is okay to cry.

Together, we can talk about your feelings and we will have counselors on hand available to talk. We recognize that we‚Äôve just started our winter break, if you would like to talk or be referred to a counselor please contact me at (405) 445-9705.

Harvey Bethany, District Administrator
Crutcho Public Schools

post_text: A Letter from our Superintendent, Dr. James Branscum:
text: A Letter from our Superintendent, Dr. James Branscum:

post_text:
Dear Crutcho Parents:

Our students will begin state testing on April 1, 2019 for grades 3rd through 8th. It is very important that our students arrive to school on time and well rested. Late students cannot be admitted to class once testing begins.

Please schedule appointments accordingly as we will not be able to accommodate student checkouts as per state law while a class is testing.

The following tips can help your student succeed on testing day.

Ensure your child eats a good breakfast ‚Äì Studies show that children perform better at school when they aren‚Äôt hungry. Crutcho offers breakfast for all students.

Help your child get enough sleep ‚Äì Your child will need to have a good night‚Äôs rest‚Ä¶
text:
Dear Crutcho Parents:

Our students will begin state testing on April 1, 2019 for grades 3rd through 8th. It is very important that our students arrive to school on time and well rested. Late students cannot be admitted to class once testing begins.

Please schedule appointments accordingly as we will not be able to accommodate student checkouts as per state law while a class is testing.

The following tips can help your student succeed on testing day.

Ensure your child eats a good breakfast ‚Äì Studies show that children perform better at school when they aren‚Äôt hungry. Crutcho offers breakfast for all students.

On behalf of Crutcho Public Schools we extend a thank you to all the citizens of the Crutcho district for the overwhelming ‚Äúyes‚Äù vote on our School Bond election. With this revenue, the District will be able to make needed air conditioning repairs; purchase laptops for our students; and a needed new bus to transport students.
